754
00:41:16,266 --> 00:41:17,834
Here we go. Start!

755
00:41:18,133 --> 00:41:20,033
It's because I blow my nose too much.

756
00:41:22,633 --> 00:41:25,400
-Should we put our things in a locker?
-You're right.

757
00:41:26,467 --> 00:41:28,567
He said he blows his nose too much?

758
00:41:29,834 --> 00:41:32,233
-Where are the lockers?
-In the back.

759
00:41:33,900 --> 00:41:36,700
THE ROOM COMES WITH A BATH,
SHOWER AND TOILET

760
00:41:37,166 --> 00:41:39,033
Kawahara looks dangerous.

761
00:41:40,767 --> 00:41:43,867
-I didn't know we could smoke here.
-You can have some of mine.

762
00:41:43,967 --> 00:41:45,133
Put that envelope away.

763
00:41:45,500 --> 00:41:47,734
-Oh, sorry.
-Give it to Fujimoto.

764
00:41:48,700 --> 00:41:49,834
Give it to him.

765
00:41:50,967 --> 00:41:51,967
Cut it out.

766
00:41:52,967 --> 00:41:54,333
Oh, Fujimoto...

767
00:41:56,867 --> 00:41:57,967
Where are the lockers?

768
00:41:58,033 --> 00:42:01,200
Fujimoto has sort of been smirking.

769
00:42:01,734 --> 00:42:03,767
-We have sushi, too.
-Look at this.

770
00:42:04,600 --> 00:42:05,934
Oh, I can...

771
00:42:06,667 --> 00:42:08,400
-He can make us sushi.
-Lucky us.

772
00:42:08,567 --> 00:42:10,066
I'll make some later.

773
00:42:10,367 --> 00:42:11,500
I don't want any of yours.

774
00:42:12,400 --> 00:42:15,934
-I don't know about your sushi.
-But my parents own a sushi restaurant.

775
00:42:18,333 --> 00:42:19,934
Put those envelopes away.

776
00:42:22,000 --> 00:42:23,900
Why is he roaming around?

777
00:42:24,300 --> 00:42:27,033
-Where did you get the envelopes?
-I bought them.

778
00:42:28,333 --> 00:42:31,100
You stole the envelopes from
Daisuke & Hanako's dressing room?

779
00:42:31,533 --> 00:42:35,166
You think I stole from them?
What would they have to steal?

780
00:42:35,467 --> 00:42:38,667
-I'm sure there's something.
-They have nothing but great jokes.

781
00:42:38,967 --> 00:42:39,967
What a square.

782
00:42:40,033 --> 00:42:42,834
-Stop fighting.
-We're not here to fight.

783
00:42:46,700 --> 00:42:48,066
Stop following me.

784
00:42:49,300 --> 00:42:50,800
Let's take turns at smoking.

785
00:42:50,900 --> 00:42:52,734
Jimmy's making a move already.

786
00:42:56,600 --> 00:42:58,333
This set is amazing.

787
00:42:58,567 --> 00:43:00,333
Fujimoto looks suspicious.

788
00:43:00,400 --> 00:43:01,500
This is a nice kitchen.

789
00:43:03,934 --> 00:43:05,100
It's amazing.

790
00:43:05,667 --> 00:43:08,333
-We can go over here, right?
-Yeah.

791
00:43:08,533 --> 00:43:10,266
-We can spread out.
-Anything goes.

792
00:43:10,633 --> 00:43:11,734
Really?

793
00:43:16,433 --> 00:43:17,767
You brought heaps.

794
00:43:19,600 --> 00:43:21,400
-Is that wine?
-Yes.

795
00:43:22,200 --> 00:43:24,266
-Drinking already?
-From the bottle?

796
00:43:24,500 --> 00:43:26,767
-You're cool.
-I'm going to drink wine.

797
00:43:27,467 --> 00:43:28,667
Just like Julie's song.

798
00:43:30,467 --> 00:43:31,967
Do you want some nibbles?

799
00:43:32,133 --> 00:43:33,967
Do you want something to nibble?

800
00:43:34,266 --> 00:43:35,467
-No, thanks.
-Okay.

801
00:43:35,533 --> 00:43:36,767
No nibbles or giggles?

802
00:43:38,800 --> 00:43:40,467
-Stop it.
-He's like a bartender.

803
00:43:42,400 --> 00:43:43,567
At a bar.

804
00:43:45,433 --> 00:43:47,433
-It's hot in here.
-This is a nice frying pan.

805
00:43:48,066 --> 00:43:50,066
Is the shower this way? Oh, it's here.

806
00:43:50,533 --> 00:43:51,533
Wow.

807
00:43:53,734 --> 00:43:54,900
They brought one in.

808
00:43:58,700 --> 00:44:00,367
Stop roaming around, Anthony.

809
00:44:03,767 --> 00:44:05,266
You're in my line of sight.

810
00:44:07,567 --> 00:44:08,633
Right?

811
00:44:12,700 --> 00:44:14,934
-We still have a long way to go.
-Yes.

812
00:44:16,233 --> 00:44:18,533
-It hasn't even been 10 minutes.
-Really?

813
00:44:19,100 --> 00:44:22,100
-We have six hours here.
-Those 10 minutes went by quickly for me.

814
00:44:22,767 --> 00:44:24,033
I agree with you.

815
00:44:24,100 --> 00:44:25,433
It's faster than I expected.

816
00:44:25,533 --> 00:44:28,600
-10 minutes have passed already?
-Not yet. It's been six.

817
00:44:28,900 --> 00:44:30,367
It's only been six minutes.

818
00:44:31,467 --> 00:44:32,367
Ohchi?

819
00:44:39,000 --> 00:44:42,133
-Are we allowed to smoke?
-You can smoke over there.

820
00:44:42,633 --> 00:44:44,000
Well, wherever.

821
00:44:44,066 --> 00:44:46,000
-Is that really alcohol?
-It is.

822
00:44:46,233 --> 00:44:47,333
It's red wine.

823
00:44:47,400 --> 00:44:48,934
-Red wine.
-Wow.

824
00:44:49,000 --> 00:44:50,233
You'd rather be drunk?

825
00:44:50,567 --> 00:44:52,066
No, I just like alcohol.

826
00:44:52,767 --> 00:44:54,767
-Were you born in Spain?
-What?

827
00:44:55,667 --> 00:44:57,300
This polo shirt is from Spain.

828
00:44:58,967 --> 00:45:01,000
I have the exact same shirt.

829
00:45:04,066 --> 00:45:05,667
But I bought mine in Okinawa.

830
00:45:06,967 --> 00:45:09,700
-As a present on a holiday.
-I got mine at the mall.

831
00:45:10,667 --> 00:45:12,333
I bought it on a family trip.

832
00:45:18,000 --> 00:45:19,233
At the hotel.

833
00:45:21,400 --> 00:45:22,333
The hotel's boutique.

834
00:45:22,633 --> 00:45:24,800
We didn't ask about your shirt.

835
00:45:24,934 --> 00:45:26,367
Do you have this shirt?

836
00:45:28,100 --> 00:45:30,300
I saw a homeless guy wearing this.

837
00:45:30,467 --> 00:45:32,433
The old guy had the very same one.

838
00:45:35,900 --> 00:45:37,033
The polo shirt.

839
00:45:39,133 --> 00:45:40,400
We all bought one.

840
00:45:41,500 --> 00:45:43,100
So, my wife has one, too.

841
00:45:43,400 --> 00:45:45,000
She has the dress version.

842
00:45:50,000 --> 00:45:52,000
-She has the dress version.
-Who does?

843
00:45:52,066 --> 00:45:55,066
-We all decided to buy the same one.
-Your wife, too?

844
00:45:55,500 --> 00:45:57,333
Do you mean your giant wife?

845
00:46:05,533 --> 00:46:07,166
It's not like she's Giant Shirota.

846
00:46:09,200 --> 00:46:10,533
She's not Giant Shirota.

847
00:46:11,967 --> 00:46:13,066
My "giant wife"?

848
00:46:16,233 --> 00:46:17,633
She's not Giant Shirota!

849
00:46:20,734 --> 00:46:21,900
This tastes great.

850
00:46:24,934 --> 00:46:26,867
Ohchi is very close. And here's Jimmy.

851
00:46:27,200 --> 00:46:28,600
They're mother and child.

852
00:46:30,400 --> 00:46:31,333
Are you hungry?

853
00:46:31,400 --> 00:46:32,667
Ohchi laughed.

854
00:46:38,467 --> 00:46:39,600
Who is it?

855
00:46:39,800 --> 00:46:40,934
Who laughed?

856
00:46:42,767 --> 00:46:43,600
Who was it?

857
00:46:44,300 --> 00:46:46,834
-Was it Jimmy?
-It's not me.

858
00:46:47,533 --> 00:46:49,367
-Seriously, who was it?
-Not me.

859
00:46:52,066 --> 00:46:53,934
-Who was it?
-Who?

860
00:47:06,233 --> 00:47:08,300
-Phew!
-He's been laughing for a while.

861
00:47:08,367 --> 00:47:10,200
-He was laughing a fair bit.
-Yes.

862
00:47:10,300 --> 00:47:13,700
He'd actually been chuckling
for quite a while.

863
00:47:14,266 --> 00:47:15,300
He was soft on you.

864
00:47:15,467 --> 00:47:18,066
-What happened?
-He was laughing the whole time.

865
00:47:18,166 --> 00:47:18,934
What was it?

866
00:47:19,000 --> 00:47:21,000
-We can laugh now, right?
-It's okay now.

867
00:47:21,066 --> 00:47:22,266
You laughed, right?

868
00:47:22,333 --> 00:47:23,667
You were chuckling, right?

869
00:47:23,734 --> 00:47:25,300
Because everyone was funny.

870
00:47:25,633 --> 00:47:27,433
We haven't said anything funny yet.

871
00:47:27,567 --> 00:47:28,667
It was nothing special.

872
00:47:28,767 --> 00:47:31,967
You guys are wandering around too much.

873
00:47:32,900 --> 00:47:35,467
-To muster up the courage.
-I want you to calm down.

874
00:47:35,967 --> 00:47:37,867
It's too early for things like that.

875
00:47:38,000 --> 00:47:39,767
He set me up.

876
00:47:40,433 --> 00:47:41,934
It's too early to set us up.

877
00:47:42,400 --> 00:47:44,500
-What are they?
-They're mother and child.

878
00:47:45,367 --> 00:47:47,433
-Mother and child.
-Are you still going?

879
00:47:47,800 --> 00:47:50,300
-So what if they're mother and child?
-She was hungry.

880
00:47:50,533 --> 00:47:51,633
Enough, please.

881
00:47:51,867 --> 00:47:53,066
Gentlemen...

882
00:47:53,934 --> 00:47:57,200
We're going to watch a replay,
just to confirm that Ohchi laughed.

883
00:47:57,734 --> 00:48:00,233
I think you know already,
but we'll play it here.

884
00:48:01,066 --> 00:48:02,600
We have video evidence.

885
00:48:03,467 --> 00:48:04,433
He was so quick.

886
00:48:04,500 --> 00:48:05,800
Let's watch the replay.

887
00:48:11,266 --> 00:48:15,133
Let's not hide our laughter with
cigarettes or drinks, okay?

888
00:48:16,166 --> 00:48:17,500
He looks like Al Capone.

889
00:48:20,033 --> 00:48:21,133
He's Al Capone.

890
00:48:21,934 --> 00:48:23,367
He's Yoshimoto's Al Capone.

891
00:48:23,567 --> 00:48:24,767
The cigarette tasted good.

892
00:48:24,867 --> 00:48:27,233
You were laughing a lot before this, too.

893
00:48:28,967 --> 00:48:30,133
Which means,

894
00:48:30,367 --> 00:48:31,867
you get a yellow card.

895
00:48:32,834 --> 00:48:34,700
You only get a yellow card for that?

896
00:48:35,000 --> 00:48:37,000
-Look.
-He's laughing hard.

897
00:48:38,633 --> 00:48:40,967
Well, I know, but...

898
00:48:41,633 --> 00:48:43,967
We've really only just started.

899
00:48:44,400 --> 00:48:47,233
-I'm safe. But if I get a red card?
-You're out.

900
00:48:47,333 --> 00:48:50,934
If he laughs at something like that,
he'll be out in no time.

901
00:48:51,100 --> 00:48:53,834
-You'd better start getting serious.
-Yes. Absolutely.

902
00:48:53,934 --> 00:48:55,567
-I got it.
-It's one million yen.

903
00:48:55,667 --> 00:48:56,900
I definitely won't laugh.

904
00:48:58,433 --> 00:48:59,400
Ouch!

905
00:48:59,734 --> 00:49:00,934
What the hell was that?

